               <p>JOSEPH NATHAN. I have an apartment in the house of Charles Lewis Israel, in <placeName id="t18340904-219-crimeloc1231">Leman-street, Whitechapel</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18340904-219-crimeloc1231" type="placeName" value="Leman-street, Whitechapel"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18340904-219-crimeloc1231" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18340904-219-off1229 t18340904-219-crimeloc1231"></join>. The prisoner is a <rs id="t18340904-219-deflabel1232" type="occupation">tailor</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18340904-219-defend1306 t18340904-219-deflabel1232"></join>, and lodged in the house about three weeks - on Thursday morning, between seven and eight o'clock, I went out as usual, and came home late in the evening - I found my box broken open, and the property in the indictment gone - it is not worth 5l. - the prisoner was gone also.</p>
               <p>CHARLES LEWIS ISRAEL. About a week after the prisoner came out of Newgate, I took him into my employ, knowing his father to be an honest man - I left him at work about eight o'clock finishing a waistcoat, and about half-past nine o'clock he left off work - I found him coming down stairs with a light in his hand - he blew out the candle - I could not see whether he had any thing - he came to my mother, and said, "How do you think I look in the<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183409040117"></xptr>waistcoat my master has given me?" - she said, "Very well" - he said he would go out and buy a pennyworth of apples - he went out and never returned - this property was missed.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18340904-219-person1309">
                  GEORGE 
                  CRAWLEY
               <interp inst="t18340904-219-person1309" type="surname" value="CRAWLEY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18340904-219-person1309" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18340904-219-person1309" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. The prisoner slept in a house in West Smithfield, and left this property there to pay for his lodging - I was called in to the place, and asked him whose the clothes were - he said, his own - I said, they were too large for him - he then said they were his father's - I took him to the station-house, and he was liberated by the inspector.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18340904-219-person1310">
                  LAWRENCE 
                  FITZHENRY
               <interp inst="t18340904-219-person1310" type="surname" value="FITZHENRY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18340904-219-person1310" type="given" value="LAWRENCE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18340904-219-person1310" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live in the house. I was told to see who was coming down stairs about half-past nine o'clock, and met the prisoner on the kitchen stairs - he had just blow the light out.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18340904-219-person1311">
                  RICHARD 
                  PRICE
               <interp inst="t18340904-219-person1311" type="surname" value="PRICE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18340904-219-person1311" type="given" value="RICHARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18340904-219-person1311" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a policeman. I had information about the prisoner, and went to his father's house - he was not there - I went next night to his father's house, and found him asleep, and took him.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>GUILTY. Aged 15. - <rs id="t18340904-219-verdict1233" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18340904-219-verdict1233" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18340904-219-verdict1233" type="verdictSubcategory" value="theftunder100s"></interp>
               Of stealing to the value of 99s.
            </rs> -</p>
